e:T4ce,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How much does drain cleaning cost in Nashville?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Standard drain cleaning in Nashville: $185 for a single fixture drain, $295 for a main line cable through the exterior cleanout, $475–$650 for hydro-jetting, and $295 for camera inspection (waived if it leads to a Sullivan-performed repair)."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Why does my main line keep backing up?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Recurring main line back-ups in Nashville are almost always tree root intrusion at the joints of older clay or cast-iron sewer laterals, or a sag/belly in the line. A camera inspection identifies which it is. Cabling and jetting buy time; permanent repair requires spot replacement or full line replacement."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you clear a clog without ripping up my floor or walls?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, in the vast majority of cases. We work through existing cleanouts, p-traps, or roof vents. We only open walls or floors when there's a confirmed broken pipe and no other access — and we'll tell you in advance if that's what's needed."}}]}6:[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BreadcrumbList\",\"itemListElement\":[{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":1,\"name\":\"Home\",\"item\":\"https://www.joebsullivanandsons.com/\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":2,\"name\":\"Services\",\"item\":\"https://www.joebsullivanandsons.com/services\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":3,\"name\":\"Drain Cleaning & Unstopping\",\"item\":\"https://www.joebsullivanandsons.com/services/drain-cleaning-unstopping\"}]}"}}],["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"$e"}}],["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"Service\",\"name\":\"Drain Cleaning & Unstopping\",\"description\":\"Drain cleaning and unstopping across Nashville. Kitchen, bath, laundry, and main line clogs cleared with cable machine, hydro-jetting, and camera diagnostics. Same-day service in most cases.\",\"serviceType\":\"Drain Cleaning & Unstopping\",\"url\":\"https://www.joebsullivanandsons.com/services/drain-cleaning-unstopping\",\"provider\":{\"@id\":\"https://www.joebsullivanandsons.com#business\"},\"areaServed\":[{\"@type\":\"City\",\"name\":\"East Nashville\"},{\"@type\":\"City\",\"name\":\"Downtown Nashville\"},{\"@type\":\"City\",\"name\":\"Green Hills\"},{\"@type\":\"City\",\"name\":\"Belle Meade & West Nashville\"},{\"@type\":\"City\",\"name\":\"Brentwood\"},{\"@type\":\"City\",\"name\":\"Franklin\"}]}"}}],["$","article",null,{"children":[["$","section",null,{"className":"py-16 lg:py-24 border-b border-ink/10","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-12 grid lg:grid-cols-12 gap-10 lg:gap-16","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"lg:col-span-7","children":[["$","nav",null,{"aria-label":"Breadcrumb","className":"text-sm text-ink-muted mb-6","children":["$","ol",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-2","children":[["$","li",null,{"children":["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/","className":"hover:text-forest","children":"Home"}]}],["$","li",null,{"aria-hidden":true,"children":"/"}],["$","li",null,{"children":["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/services","className":"hover:text-forest","children":"Services"}]}],["$","li",null,{"aria-hidden":true,"children":"/"}],["$","li",null,{"className":"text-ink","children":"Drain Cleaning"}]]}]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"eyebrow mb-4","children":"Service"}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl leading-[1.05] text-ink mb-6","children":["Drain Cleaning & Unstopping"," ",["$","span",null,{"className":"italic text-forest","children":"in Nashville"}]]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"font-display italic text-2xl text-ink-soft mb-7","children":"Clog cleared. No mess left behind."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg text-ink-muted leading-relaxed","children":"Sullivan has cleared more drains across Nashville than we can count — kitchen sinks, bathroom lavatories, tub and shower drains, toilet stoppages, laundry standpipes, and main sewer line back-ups. We use cable machines for everyday clogs, hydro-jetting for grease and root intrusion, and a sewer camera when we need to see exactly what's happening fifty feet down the line. Most residential drain calls get same-day service."}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"lg:col-span-5","children":["$","$Lf",null,{"defaultService":"drain-cleaning-unstopping"}]}]]}]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"py-16 lg:py-24","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"prose-editorial","children":[["$","div","Cable machine vs. hydro-jet: which you actually need",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Cable machine vs. hydro-jet: which you actually need"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"A cable (snake) machine handles the majority of drain clogs — hair in bathroom drains, kitchen sink grease blockages within 25 feet of the cleanout, and most toilet stoppages. Hydro-jetting uses high-pressure water (3,000–4,000 PSI) to cut through heavier grease deposits, scale buildup in older pipes, and tree-root intrusion in main sewer lines. We default to a cable machine because it's faster and cheaper; we recommend the jetter when the camera shows recurring grease or root issues that cabling won't actually resolve. Honest answer first, machine second."}]]}],["$","div","Main line back-ups: what's actually happening",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Main line back-ups: what's actually happening"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When every drain in the house is slow at once and a toilet flushes water up into the shower or tub, you have a main sewer line back-up — not individual drain clogs. The most common Nashville cause is tree root intrusion at the joints of older clay or cast-iron sewer laterals, especially in East Nashville, Belmont-Hillsboro, and Sylvan Park neighborhoods where mature trees and 1920s–1950s sewer pipe are common. We cable and camera the line, identify the root location, and either jet-clean (buys you 2–4 years before the next event) or recommend a sewer line repair or replacement (permanent fix). We never push the replacement when cleaning will hold."}]]}],["$","div","Camera inspection: when it's worth it",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Camera inspection: when it's worth it"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"A sewer camera inspection is worth the cost ($295 in the Nashville metro) when: you've had two or more main-line back-ups in 12 months, you're buying a house with a sewer line older than 1970, or you're trying to decide between repeated cleaning and a one-time line replacement. We record the inspection and email you the video, with marked timestamps for any defects we find. Some Nashville real estate transactions include a sewer camera as part of the inspection contingency — we do those routinely."}]]}],["$","div","Pricing and policy",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing and policy"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Standard drain cleaning in Nashville: $185 for a kitchen, bath, or laundry drain via cleanout access, $245 for a toilet pull-and-clear, $295 for a main line cable through an exterior cleanout, $475–$650 for hydro-jetting depending on line size and length, $295 for camera inspection (waived if it leads to a repair we perform). We never use chemical drain cleaners — they damage older Nashville pipe (especially galvanized and cast iron). Same-day service in most cases; we'll tell you the actual ETA when you call."}]]}]]}]}]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"bg-bone-100/60 border-y border-ink/10 py-16 lg:py-24","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"eyebrow mb-3","children":"Common questions"}],["$","h2",null,{"className":"font-display text-3xl lg:text-4xl text-ink mb-10 leading-tight","children":["Frequently asked about ","drain cleaning"," in Nashville."]}],["$","dl",null,{"className":"space-y-6","children":[["$","div","How much does drain cleaning cost in Nashville?",{"className":"card-press p-6","children":[["$","dt",null,{"className":"font-display text-xl text-ink mb-3","children":"How much does drain cleaning cost in Nashville?"}],["$","dd",null,{"className":"text-ink-muted leading-relaxed","children":"Standard drain cleaning in Nashville: $185 for a single fixture drain, $295 for a main line cable through the exterior cleanout, $475–$650 for hydro-jetting, and $295 for camera inspection (waived if it leads to a Sullivan-performed repair)."}]]}],["$","div","Why does my main line keep backing up?",{"className":"card-press p-6","children":[["$","dt",null,{"className":"font-display text-xl text-ink mb-3","children":"Why does my main line keep backing up?"}],["$","dd",null,{"className":"text-ink-muted leading-relaxed","children":"Recurring main line back-ups in Nashville are almost always tree root intrusion at the joints of older clay or cast-iron sewer laterals, or a sag/belly in the line. A camera inspection identifies which it is. Cabling and jetting buy time; permanent repair requires spot replacement or full line replacement."}]]}],["$","div","Can you clear a clog without ripping up my floor or walls?",{"className":"card-press p-6","children":[["$","dt",null,{"className":"font-display text-xl text-ink mb-3","children":"Can you clear a clog without ripping up my floor or walls?"}],["$","dd",null,{"className":"text-ink-muted leading-relaxed","children":"Yes, in the vast majority of cases. We work through existing cleanouts, p-traps, or roof vents. We only open walls or floors when there's a confirmed broken pipe and no other access — and we'll tell you in advance if tha